===============================================================================
OVERVIEW

  modes_db_2_gpx is a simple hack to convert modes_rx (https://github.com/bistromath/gr-air-modes) sqlite database data into GPX XML based data which can be load
  into programs such as viking (http://viking.sourceforge.net/) or marble (http://marble.kde.org/).

===============================================================================
REQUIREMENTS
  modes_db_2_gpx requires:
    * CMake 2.8 or later
    * SQLite 3.7 or later
    * Boost 1.40 or later

========================================================================
BUILDING

  $ cd build
  $ cmake ../
  $ make

========================================================================
USAGE

  The main application is modes_db_2_gpx. For a complete list of options,
  run:

  $ modes_db_2_gpx --help

  By default modes_db_2_gpx will try to open 'air_modes.db' and will generate 'air_modes.gpx'
  this behaviour can be overridden.
